Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants to trigger an action when the device "KDR2-CAN LTS_SW" sends a physical command "Fast On" (COC event).
2. The condition is to detect the "Fast On" command sent by "KDR2-CAN LTS_SW".
3. The action is to turn on the "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW" device with 75% brightness.
4. The ramp rate for "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW" should be set to "Fast". The fastest ramp rate enum is 0.1 seconds [31], so we will use that.
5. The commands to send are:
   - Set Ramp Rate [RR] to 31 (0.1 seconds)
   - Turn On [DON] with parameter 75 (75%)

This is a single-level automation with one condition and two actions executed sequentially.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on foyer light fast when KDR2-CAN LTS_SW fast on",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "KDR2-CAN LTS_SW",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Ramp Rate", "value": 31, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW",
        "command": "On",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "On", "value": 75, "uom": "percent", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
